ideally, if in a big city and later traveling to smaller ones, try signing up for an account with smaller banks like woori bank or ping an bank; these offer free inter-bank atm withdrawals anywhere in china (ping an bank also offers free withdrawals overseas, a plus if traveling to nearby countries later). alternatively, travelex offers unionpay cash passports in certain countries. costs[edit] while china is no longer the bargain destination it was during the 1990's, it remains quite affordable. unless you are heading to hong kong or macau, the mainland is generally much less expensive - from a traveler's 